  "texts": [
    "According to Liu et al.",
    "(85), most of the dose difference caused by sCTs occurs at the distal end of the proton beam due to errors along the beam path on the planning CT. As a result, the tumour could be substantially underdosed or Organs at risk overdosed.",
    "According to Liu et al.",
    "(85, 86), the largest absolute difference observed among patients with liver cancer is 0.56 cm, while for those with prostate cancer, the mean absolute difference is 0.75 cm.",
    "Besides assessing dosimetric accuracy for treatment planning, geometric fidelity is another essential consideration."
  ]
}